name: NonLiveBirthICD10PCSProcedures
title: Non Live Birth ICD10PCS Procedures
description: For Contraceptive eCQMs Approval for Trial Use application in Spring 2022; This set of values contains codes indicating non-live births (i.e., ectopic pregnancies, intrauterine fetal demise, early pregnancy loss, abortion).
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Family Planning - provision of most and moderately effective contraceptive methods, access to long-acting reversible contraception (LARC), among postpartum females ages 15-44),(Data Element Scope: Procedure codes indicating non-live births (i.e., ectopic pregnancies, intrauterine fetal demise, early pregnancy loss, abortion)),(Inclusion Criteria: Procedure codes indicating non-live births (i.e., ectopic pregnancies, intrauterine fetal demise, early pregnancy loss, abortion)),(Exclusion Criteria: Excluding live birth deliveries)
